	<table width="100%" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" border="0">
	<td bgcolor="#4D4D73"><img src="images/posticon.gif" border="0" alt="Old Post"></td><td width="100%" bgcolor="#4D4D73"><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
	Posted 12-01-2004 <font color="#FEDE01">06:12 AM</font></font></td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">About 6 or so months ago my guild on the Morden Rasp server had a raid against Vox, which ended up not going too well.  After the guild leader had logged for the night, he was never heard from again.  I don't want to just assume it was because the raid failed, since something might have come up in real life and what not, but there is still a problem left behind by this...  He's still listed as the leader of the guild, and takes up one of the leader positions.<br />
<br />
During a week long absense I had due to internet problems, I logged back in to find my guild was down to about 12 people, as the officers of my guild had told everyone that we were merging with another guild on the server.  So, we were down at 12 people, had no officers, and had no active leader.   But, the 12 of us perservered, and we eventually got the GMs to appoint one of us as the guild leader.  From their we were free to re-invite some of the people who didn't like their new guild (which also ran itself into the ground a month or two after), and we reformed our guild and began growing again.  A couple months ago we had a merger happen, which saw us pretty much absorb another guild into ours, and it worked out terrific.  They were a small dedicated group of people, as were we, and we continued to grow still.<br />
<br />
Zoom forwards to this very day.  Our guild and another guild are in talks of a merger, as they had lost a lot of people in the past few weeks, and are dying to join up with someone.  We already have two active leaders in our guild, and the former leader who is still there (who still hasn't logged in since May or thereabouts).  In the event that the merger works really well, and in the event that the leader of the other guild is made a leader of ours, the problem arises...<br />
<br />
How in the heck do you get rid of a leader who hasn't logged in for more than half a year?  The GMs won't do it for us, and we don't want to all disband and lose our guild name.  Anyone have any suggestions?<br />
<br />
(by the way, sorry to bore you with my guilds history... I figured a good back story was needed)</font></p>
	
	<p><p><img src="/forums/images/sig_separator.gif" width="282" height="11" Alt="Hey! Watch where you point that thing!"><br>
<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">

63 Cleric on Morden Rasp<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1100194" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1100194</a>
</font></p></p>
	<p></p>
	</td></tr></table>
