	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><table border="0" align="center" width="90%" cellpadding="3" cellspacing="1"><tr><td><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#FFFFFF"><b>quote:</b></font></td></tr><tr><td style="BORDER: #000000 1px solid; FONT-SIZE: 11px; COLOR: #FFFFFF; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana,Arial; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #4D4D73;">Leapy said in post <a href="http://www.eqcleric.com/forums/showthread.php?s=&postid=#post" target="_blank">#4 </a>:<br />
<b>Well, I don't know if I'd say he was the man in charge ever... Our original guld leaser had to quit playing and promoted someone to leadership.  This was the guy who hasn't shown up, and he was leader for about 3 weeks before he decided not to show up.  Grr... If someone is just gonna pack up and leave Everquest one day, and they are a leader of a guild, why not be courteous and drop yourself from the position?  Some people have no morals. </b></td></tr></table> <br />
Well, as I said before, I agree that this guy is rather inconsiderate to have done this to your guild.  You're exactly right...if he wasn't planning on returning, he should've turned the GL-ship over to somebody else...just as the previous GL apparently did to him.<br />
<br />
But, I meant he's "the man in charge" in the sense that he has the ability to just log on and type /guilddisband, and then where would you be?  Scrambling to reform your guild, sending petitions to the GMs for a new guild tag (which, as I warned you, can take upwards of three weeks or so ).  I was just saying I personally wouldn't risk sinking a lot of effort into building up a guild with that possibility (even if it's a slim chance) hanging over my head.</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
	<p><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#FFFFFF"><i>Last edited by Evanya on 12-01-2004 at 06:23 PM</i></font></p>
