	<!-- Main Post Body -->
	<table width="100%" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" border="0">
	<td bgcolor="#4D4D73"><img src="images/posticon.gif" border="0" alt="Old Post"></td><td width="100%" bgcolor="#4D4D73"><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
	Posted 12-02-2004 <font color="#FEDE01">11:03 AM</font></font></td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">This happened to me in 2001.<br />
<br />
I was a member of a guild called the Blood Cult Clan.  It was a lowbie guild and it had been going through some problems.  The guild name and title belonged to a guy called Warclaw (iksar warrior) who'd disappeared - it later transpired that he was a marine and he'd been posted overseas with no access to the internet.<br />
<br />
We held elections and I was chosen as the new guild leader.  We disbanded the Blood Cult Clan and formed a new guild which was simply called Blood Cult.  At that time, we were down to 12 members, levels 46-54; we seriously doubted if we were ever going to be able to raid a plane (plane-raids meant uberness at the time, the top guild on the server was just making its early forays into Sleeper's Tomb.)<br />
<br />
Thanks to some excellent officers, I was able to rebuild the guild during Luclin.  Although I left the guild for personal reasons some months later, BC was third guild into Time on Xev iirc; when I quit EQ, the guild was happily ploughing through the Ikkinz raid cycle.</font></p>
	
	<p><p><img src="/forums/images/sig_separator.gif" width="282" height="11" Alt="Hey! Watch where you point that thing!"><br>
<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">

What on earth is <a href="http://yexx.proboards39.com" target="_blank">Yexx</a> ?
</font></p></p>
	<p></p>
	</td></tr></table>
